---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout title="REST quickstart · flipagent docs">
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>REST quickstart</h1>
				<p class="lead">flipagent exposes one unified surface under <code>/v1/*</code>. Responses are flipagent-native (cents-int Money, ISO 8601 timestamps, lowercase status enums, <code>marketplace</code> on every record). Future Amazon / Mercari adapters reuse the same paths via the <code>marketplace</code> parameter.</p>

				<h2>Search active listings</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`curl "https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/items/search?q=canon%2050mm&limit=5" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx"`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Returns a normalized <code>ItemSearchResponse</code> (<code>items[]</code>, <code>limit</code>, <code>offset</code>, optional <code>total</code>) with cents-int Money and a <code>marketplace</code> tag on every record.</p>

				<h2>Listing detail</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`curl "https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/items/v1%7C123456789%7C0" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx"`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Accepts any id form: bare numeric, eBay v1 (<code>v1|123|0</code>), or the full <code>ebay.com/itm/...</code> URL.</p>

				<h2>Sold listings (last 90 days)</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`curl "https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/items/search?q=canon%2050mm&status=sold&limit=50" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx"`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Same shape as active; sold-only entries carry <code>soldAt</code>, <code>soldPrice</code>, <code>soldQuantity</code>.</p>

				<h2>Score one listing</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`curl -X POST "https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/evaluate" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{"itemId": "v1|123456789|0", "opts": {"minNetCents": 2000}}'`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>One call answers "should I flip this?". The server fetches the item, finds real recent sales of the same product, ignores listings that aren't actually the same item, and returns a <code>rating: "buy" | "hold" | "skip"</code> plus the math behind it. Response shape: <code>{`{ item, evaluation, market, sold, active, filter, returns, meta, ... }`}</code>. <code>evaluation</code> carries the rating, signals, and the recommended exit price. <code>sold</code> + <code>active</code> are pre-rolled digests (distribution, histogram, cadence, recent trend, condition mix) — prefer these over the heavier <code>soldPool</code> / <code>activePool</code> arrays kept for back-compat. <code>filter</code> reports kept/rejected counts. <code>meta</code> reports transport + cache provenance. Drill into individual rejected listings via <code>GET /v1/evaluate/&#123;itemId&#125;/pool</code>.</p>

				<h2>Forwarder quote</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`curl -X POST "https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/ship/quote" \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer fa_free_xxx" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{"item": {...}, "forwarder": {"destState": "NY", "weightG": 500}}'`}</code></pre></div>

				<h2>Use it from Node</h2>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`const res = await fetch(
  "https://api.flipagent.dev/v1/items/search?q=canon%2050mm",
  { headers: { Authorization: \`Bearer \${process.env.FLIPAGENT_API_KEY}\` } }
);
const { items, total } = await res.json();`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Or use <a href="/docs/quickstart/"><code>@flipagent/sdk</code></a> for typed namespaces.</p>

				<h2>Response headers</h2>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Header</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td><code>X-RateLimit-Limit</code></td><td>Credit budget for your tier.</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code></td><td>Credits left in the current period.</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>X-RateLimit-Reset</code></td><td>ISO-8601 timestamp of the next reset (paid tiers only).</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>X-Flipagent-Credits-Charged</code></td><td>Credits this call cost.</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>X-Flipagent-From-Cache</code></td><td><code>true</code> when the response was served from cache instead of a fresh fetch.</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2>Errors</h2>
				<p>JSON body with <code>error</code> + optional <code>message</code>. Common codes:</p>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Body.error</th><th>Cause</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>400</td><td><code>validation_failed</code></td><td>Body / query failed schema validation.</td></tr>
						<tr><td>401</td><td><code>unauthorized</code> / <code>invalid_key</code></td><td>Missing or revoked key.</td></tr>
						<tr><td>429</td><td><code>credits_exceeded</code></td><td>Monthly credit budget exhausted.</td></tr>
						<tr><td>429</td><td><code>burst_rate_limited</code></td><td>Per-minute or per-hour burst cap hit.</td></tr>
						<tr><td>502</td><td><code>upstream_failed</code></td><td>The upstream marketplace call failed. Usually transient; retry once.</td></tr>
						<tr><td>503</td><td><code>billing_not_configured</code></td><td>Stripe isn't enabled on the server. Hosted users won't see this.</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
